Description: Upper body sherd of East Greek, probably Aeolian, grey ware pottery vessel, possibly an oinochoe or dinos; interior: reserved; exterior: dark grey slip and inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: There is a modern incised inscription 'Diosk' on interior indicates findspot. The fabric finds parallels with British Museum 1888,0601.637 which was analysed with NAA by Hans Mommsen (Bonn). The results placed the fabric (sample NAUK 64) in NAA group G and the origin was determined to be Aeolis.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.158)
